<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900419-0059</DOCNO><DOCID>900419-0059.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- MCI Communications Corp.:   First-Quarter Profit Rose   21% on 20% Revenue Gain</HL><DATE>04/19/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6</SO><CO>   MCIC</CO><IN>TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   MCI Communications Corp., Washington, reportedfirst-quarter net income increased 21% with strong growth inrevenue and long-distance telephone traffic volume.   The long-distance carrier said net income grew to $163million, or 62 cents a share, from $135 million, or 51 centsa share, in the year-earlier quarter.</LP><TEXT>   Revenue increased 20% to $1.81 billion from $1.5 billion.   Analysts said results were consistent with theirpredictions. Joel Gross of Donaldson Lufkin andamp; Jenrette saidMCI &quot;is gaining market share and will continue to do so.&quot;Jack Grubman of PaineWebber said results were &quot;fine,&quot; but thestock isn't going up because MCI &quot;is getting penalized fordoing the right thing.&quot; He said the company is investing forthe long term in marketing, sales efforts, equipment andnetwork improvements.   In national over-the-counter trading, MCI stock closed at$35.125, down $1.625.</TEXT></DOC>